t.com/images/2026/06/07/magazine/07mag-ididit-sleep/07mag-ididit-sleep-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Photo illustration by Hannah Whitaker</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Tesla Driver Using Autopilot Crashes Into Home in Texas and Kills a Woman, Officials Say</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The driver told investigators he was using the vehicle’s automated-driver system when the vehicle left the roadway and crashed into a house in Harris County, Texas.</description><dc:creator>Johnny Diaz</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:49:15 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Driverless Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Self-Driving Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fatalities</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">casualties</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Crash</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Harris County</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Katy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/21/multimedia/21xp-tesla-vtmq/21xp-tesla-vtmq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mike Blake/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>The dashboard of a Tesla model using a driver-assistance system in California.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Larry Sanger, a Wikipedia Founder, Is Barred From Editing on the Site</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A vote to bar Larry Sanger indefinitely from the volunteer community of Wikipedia came days after he submitted a proposal on “intellectual diversity.”</description><dc:creator>Adeel Hassan</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 11:48:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Wikipedia</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-eafs</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/24/multimedia/24xp-wikipedia/24xp-wikipedia-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ulli Winkler/ullstein bild, via Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>Larry Sanger said that Wikipedia was “one of the most effective organs of establishment propaganda in history.”</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>‘Hard Fork’ Live, Part 3: Differing Visions of an A.I. Future</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>One final episode from our live event, featuring a debate, questions from listeners and the dramatic and unplanned collapse of a dancing robot.</description><dc:creator>Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Rachel Cohn, Whitney Jones, Vjeran Pavic, Alyssa Moxley, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano, Rowan Niemisto and Diane Wong</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 11:00:03 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">science</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Robot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Dwarkesh Patel</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-audio</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/19/podcasts/19hardfork-live-part-3/19hardfork-live-part-3-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.png" medium="image"><media:credit>Photo Illustration by The New York Times. Photo: Mike Kai Chen for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Chinese A.I. Models Gain Ground on Anthropic and OpenAI</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/zai-china-artificial-intelligence-models.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/zai-china-artificial-intelligence-models.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/zai-china-artificial-intelligence-models.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Silicon Valley engineers recently flocked to new technology from a Chinese company, Z.ai, that is almost as good as its American competitors but much cheaper.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz, Karen Weise and Meaghan Tobin</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 15:34:41 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cloud computing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Z.ai</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DeepSeek</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/24/24visualUploader-87422-cover/24visualUploader-87422-cover-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image" /></item><item><title>Your Home Could Help Solve AI’s Growing Power Demand</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/24/business/energy-environment/ai-data-centers-tesla.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/24/business/energy-environment/ai-data-centers-tesla.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/24/business/energy-environment/ai-data-centers-tesla.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Tesla, Sunrun and Renew Home plan to tap solar panels, batteries, thermostats and other devices installed in millions of homes to meet the energy demands of artificial intelligence.</description><dc:creator>Ivan Penn</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 09:02:13 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric power</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Energy Efficiency</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Solar energy</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Batteries</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Thermostat</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Home Improvement</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Renew Home</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sunrun</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/24/multimedia/24biz-distributed-energy-1-lcmh/24biz-distributed-energy-1-lcmh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Collin Chappelle for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Installation of a Sunrun solar panel on a roof in California. Sunrun is working with Tesla and Renew Home to use home energy devices to help data centers get online faster.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>How to Remove Apps You Never Use (or at Least Hide Them)</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>If you need space back on your phone or tablet, removing built-in and unused apps can help free up storage and reduce screen clutter.</description><dc:creator>J. D. Biersdorfer</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 09:02:01 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Smartphone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tablet computer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">None</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Android</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Samsung</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.co