ww.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">casualties</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Katy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/22/multimedia/22biz-tesla-crash-1-cbhp/22biz-tesla-crash-1-cbhp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mike Blake/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Tesla’s driver-assistance systems have been implicated in a number of accidents, some of them fatal.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>China Takes Supercomputer Crown From U.S. For First Time Since 2017</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/23/technology/china-supercomputer-crown-us.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/23/technology/china-supercomputer-crown-us.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/23/technology/china-supercomputer-crown-us.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A supercomputer in Shenzhen was declared the world’s fastest. It uses only standard microprocessors and not the special-purpose chips called graphics processing units.</description><dc:creator>Don Clark</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2026 09:02:27 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Supercomputer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">International relations</category><category domain="ht